mouse in the grass from a mile away. Similarly, cats
have the extraordinary ability to see in the dark. Through
natural s election over time, these animals have developed
visual systems uniquely adapted to their way of life. The
human visual system has also adapted to many things
well. Although our night vis ion is not as good as that
of a cat, our color vision is excellent. This is not a bad
tradeoff, s ince being able to enjoy a sunset’s beauty
seems worth an occasional fall in the dark.

#2008 9월 45번
