change her mind. Then, my parenting class teacher
recommended that I should give her rewards. So
I used this simple phrase, which worked wonders: “If you
go and brush your teeth now, we will have time to read
three stories instead of just one.” Whenever she heard it,
she would jump up and brush her teeth right away.

